import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.dropna()
    plt.hist(data['open'], bins=20, color='blue', alpha=0.5)
    plt.axvline(data['open'].mean(), color='red', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Mean: {data['open'].mean():0.2f}")
    plt.axvline(data['open'].median(), color='green', linestyle='dashed', linewidth=1, label=f"Median: {data['open'].median():0.2f}")
    plt.xlabel('Open Prices')
    plt.ylabel('Frequency')
    plt.legend()
    plt.title("What is the distribution of 'open' prices?", wrap=True)
    plt.xticks(rotation=45)
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data['date'] = pd.to_datetime(data['date'], format='%Y-%m-%d', errors='coerce')
    data = data[pd.notna(data['date'])]
    fig, ax = plt.subplots(figsize=(10, 6))
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['open'], label='Open')
    ax.plot(data['date'], data['close'], label='Close')
    ax.set_xlabel('Date')
    ax.set_ylabel('Price')
    ax.set_title("What is the relationship between 'open' and 'close' prices?")
    ax.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
```

import matplotlib.pyplot as plt
import pandas as pd

def plot(data: pd.DataFrame):
    data = data.copy()
    data['count'] = 1
    signal_counts = data.groupby('signal').count()['count']
    signal_counts.plot(kind='bar', color='blue')
    plt.title("What is the distribution of 'signal' values?", wrap=True)
    plt.xlabel('Signal')
    plt.ylabel('Count')
    plt.legend()
    return plt

chart = plot(data)
